{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851940992,"sessionID":"ses_286fa1272ffeJLsxXpclIzkNF4","part":{"id":"prt_d79062182001IDmeM7xF7Ni9vv","messageID":"msg_d79061172001bgwfXASwISargj","sessionID":"ses_286fa1272ffeJLsxXpclIzkNF4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_922a410efafa40dfba7da412","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement Redis storage backend for the `Store` interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage keyed by session ID with expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The agentcube system requires a Redis-backed storage implementation for session management. The `Store` interface was defined in AR-012; this AR implements the Redis provider using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`.\n12: \n13: ### Goal\n14: \n15: Implement `redisStore` in `pkg/store` with:\n16: - Full `Store` interface implementation\n17: - Sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking\n18: - Pipeline-based atomic operations\n19: - Configuration via environment variables\n20: \n21: ### Value\n22: - Production-ready Redis backend for session storage\n23: - Efficient session garbage collection via indexed queries\n24: - Atomic operations ensuring data consistency\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In-Scope\n31: \n32: | Deliverable | Description |\n33: |-------------|-------------|\n34: | `store_redis.go` | Redis store implementation |\n35: | `redisStore` struct | Client, key prefixes, ZSET keys |\n36: | `makeRedisOptions` | Parse REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD |\n37: | All Store methods | Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n38: \n39: ### Code Structure\n40: \n41: ```\n42: pkg/store/\n43: ├── store_redis.go    # Redis implementation\n44: ├── store.go          # Store interface (AR-012)\n45: ├── singleton.go      # Storage() singleton (AR-012)\n46: ├── errors.go         # ErrNotFound (AR-012)\n47: └── types.go          # Store type constants (AR-012)\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Configuration\n51: \n52: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n53: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n54: | REDIS_ADDR | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n55: | REDIS_PASSWORD | Yes* | - | Redis password |\n56: | REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n57: | STORE_TYPE | No | redis | Set to \"redis\" for Redis backend |\n58: \n59: *Required unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n60: \n61: ### Key Patterns\n62: \n63: | Key | Pattern | Type |\n64: |-----|---------|------|\n65: | Session data | `session:{sessionID}` | String (JSON) |\n66: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` | ZSET (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n67: | Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` | ZSET (score = activity Unix) |\n68: \n69: ### Out-of-Scope\n70: - Valkey implementation (separate AR)\n71: - Connection pooling configuration\n72: - Redis Sentinel/Cluster support\n73: - Data encryption at rest\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Impact Analysis\n78: \n79: ### Dependencies\n80: \n81: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n82: |------------|--------|---------|\n83: | github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 | ^9.x | Redis client |\n84: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types | local | SandboxInfo type |\n85: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging |\n86: \n87: ### Upstream\n88: \n89: - **AR-012 Store Interface** — Interface contract to implement\n90: - **pkg/common/types** — Provides SandboxInfo struct\n91: \n92: ### Downstream Consumers\n93: \n94: 1. **Session Manager** — CRUD operations\n95: 2. **Garbage Collector** — ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes\n96: 3. **Health Checks** — Ping for connectivity\n97: \n98: ### Risks\n99: \n100: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n101: |------|----------|------------|\n102: | Redis unavailable | High | Ping on startup, health checks |\n103: | Data inconsistency | Medium | Pipeline for atomic operations |\n104: | Password exposure | Medium | Require explicit opt-in for empty password |\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Alternatives Considered\n109: \n110: ### Option 1: Direct Redis Commands (Selected)\n111: \n112: **Approach**: Use go-redis/v9 client directly with pipeline for atomic operations.\n113: \n114: **Pros**:\n115: - Mature, well-maintained client\n116: - Built-in connection pooling\n117: - Pipeline support for atomic batches\n118: - Familiar Kubernetes patterns\n119: \n120: **Cons**:\n121: - Additional dependency\n122: \n123: **Decision**: Selected — industry standard for Redis in Go.\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### Option 2: Redis Cluster Mode\n128: \n129: **Approach**: Use Redis Cluster for distributed setup.\n130: \n131: **Pros**:\n132: - Horizontal scaling\n133: - High availability\n134: \n135: **Cons**:\n136: - Key hashing requirements (same slot)\n137: - More complex deployment\n138: \n139: **Decision**: Deferred — single Redis instance meets current scale.\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ## Implementation Plan\n144: \n145: ### Phase 1: Struct and Options\n146: - [ ] Define `redisStore` struct with client, key prefixes\n147: - [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions` for env var parsing\n148: - [ ] Add password validation\n149: \n150: ### Phase 2: Core Operations\n151: - [ ] Implement `Ping` — PING → expect PONG\n152: - [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` — GET session:{id}\n153: - [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox` — Pipeline: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n154: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox` — SET key value XX\n155: \n156: ### Phase 3: Deletion and Updates\n157: - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — Pipeline: DEL, ZREM both indexes\n158: - [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity` — GET verify exists, ZADD\n159: \n160: ### Phase 4: Listing\n161: - [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` — ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry, then GET\n162: - [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` — ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity, then GET\n163: - [ ] Handle orphan ZSET entries gracefully\n164: \n165: ### Phase 5: Lifecycle\n166: - [ ] Implement `Close` — cli.Close()\n167: \n168: ### Phase 6: Testing\n169: - [ ] Unit tests for each method\n170: - [ ] Test key construction\n171: - [ ] Test error cases (not found, nil input, validation)\n172: \n173: ---\n174: \n175: ## Acceptance Criteria\n176: \n177: - [ ] `redisStore` implements full `Store` interface\n178: - [ ] `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` correctly configure client\n179: - [ ] Password required unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n180: - [ ] Session key format: `session:{id}`\n181: - [ ] Expiry index: ZSET with score = ExpiresAt.Unix()\n182: - [ ] Last-activity index: ZSET with score = time.Now().Unix() on store\n183: - [ ] StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n184: - [ ] UpdateSandbox requires existing key (XX flag)\n185: - [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from all indexes\n186: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries by expiry time\n187: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries by last activity\n188: - [ ] Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n189: - [ ] Nil sandbox rejected with error\n190: - [ ] Empty session ID rejected on UpdateSessionLastActivity\n191: - [ ] Close properly terminates connection\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Redis storage backend for the `Store` interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage keyed by session ID with expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires a Redis-backed storage implementation for session management. The `Store` interface was defined in AR-012; this AR implements the Redis provider using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement `redisStore` in `pkg/store` with:\n- Full `Store` interface implementation\n- Sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking\n- Pipeline-based atomic operations\n- Configuration via environment variables\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775851940973,"end":1775851940990}}}}
